&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Here's the long version &lt;/STRONG&gt;- Cleric and Paladin stuns share similar mana cost, cast times, and duration (that 25% extra duration you seem so fond of translates into a stun potentially sticking on a mob .5 seconds more).&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;So in that aspect they are similar.&amp;nbsp; However, to state they "work the same" is a huge fallacy.&amp;nbsp; First difference is the resist adjustment.&amp;nbsp; You state this is "insignificant".&amp;nbsp; I'll remember that as the mob bolts away from me after resisting the stun.&amp;nbsp; So even if the mob flees and your stuns are resisted, what do you do? -- Cast your root that works the same as the cleric one?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Oh wait, it doesn't work the same as the cleric one.&amp;nbsp; First difference is mana cost.&amp;nbsp; Yours: 75 mana.&amp;nbsp; Clerics: 180 mana.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Second difference is cast time.&amp;nbsp; Yours: .75.&amp;nbsp; Clerics:&amp;nbsp; 2.5.&amp;nbsp; Third difference is how a paladin and cleric must "finish off" this mob.&amp;nbsp; The cleric in order to damage a mob faster than it regens must use procs, nukes, or the ward (I guess could click off ward and not attack it..let it kill itself on marks....but we'd have to rez ourselves after we fell asleep at the keyboard before it died).&amp;nbsp; How do you finish off your mobs, melee - melee, stun, stun, melee --if your root breaks, you have more stuns available and a faster root to stop it.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;However, I do not intend this post as a "waah waaah" paladins get something we don't.&amp;nbsp; Rather it is a, Sir - what you posted is wrong and here is the proof.&amp;nbsp; Our stuns and roots do not work the same...end of story.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
