      <title>Re: snare plus 1700 pt chromostrike for the win ALex</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10846#M10846</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;That's good advice!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I don't know if anyone can suggest better; if we want to improve it any more, we'll have to get a better breakdown of how the goblin soloing in Stillmoon is failing you, what gear you are using and what spells, etc.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I recently switched my root from the 3 minute to the 1 minute, and have found it works much better.&amp;nbsp; This is a good idea, and one I had overlooked for too long.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I cannot stress enough (nor agree enough) that nuking while soloing is, for the most part, a colossal waste of mana. I usually only nuke when I am in a group and not expecting to take any hits.&amp;nbsp; One cast of Ward of Retribution, when soloing, is going to far outdamage any single nuke I can throw.&amp;nbsp; My best nuke, right now, lands for 4024 against an undead mob.&amp;nbsp; That's a crit with full Destructive Fury AAs and an augment DD focus.&amp;nbsp; Against living critters, the crit range is usually in the 3300 range or so.&amp;nbsp; While I may be able to get two or three nukes off for the same cost of one Ward of Retribution, even at only 8 procs&amp;nbsp;a minute, I'm still looking at a minimum of ~4400 damage (550 damage x 8), and potentially much more than that if I get a couple of crit hits.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Nuking, when soloing, is plain and simple a bad idea.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Another big aid to soloing is going to be any investment in avoidance AAs.&amp;nbsp; I also cannot stress those enough.&amp;nbsp; When you consider that the ward can process on any swing (hit or miss) and you can boost your avoidance up considerably with AAs, it's pretty clear to me anyway how you can easily improve your solo capability.&amp;nbsp; You do not even need to have Anguish or Time gear for this -- just time to invest in those AAs.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Kilva's Skin of Flame potions are also an excellent kick for soloing; when you pair them with Mark of the Blameless and Mark of Retribution, you end up with a fantastic porcupine effect.&amp;nbsp; I'm by no means a rich cleric, but I can afford paying 400-500pp for a 10 dose Kilva's Skin of Flame.&amp;nbsp; If you visit a place like the Plane of Hate, or even if you go to Sebilis or Velketor's for one dose's duration of this potion, you are fairly likely to earn a good chunk of the cost back.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've gone to Hate for a few hours and come back with nearly 2k of raw coin &amp;amp; gems and rewards from the armour turnin quests.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think any cleric can solo.. it just takes time to gain the experience (knowing when you need to heal, what spells to use and when), and the knowledge to maximize your strengths (ward damage, quick healing) and minimize your weaknesses (lack of snare, lack of slow). Heck, I'd even say lack of slow is not a weakness at all any more. The LAST thing I want is a mob taking fewer swings at me.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Soloing doesn't have to be every cleric's cup of tea. However, I don't think it's fair to declare clerics to be woefully underpowered as soloers when, in my opinion, we have some rather unique strengths that make soloing a viable and entertaining option for me when I play this game.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
